          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".NU WAS CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND COUNTS, DEAD TIME",
                " LOSSES, SPURIOUS FISSION, VARIATION OF THE",
                " SCINTILLATOR EFFICIENCY WITH THE FISSION COUNTER",
                " POSITION, CHANGES IN THE COUNTER EFFICIENCY WITH",
                " THE BACKGROUND RATE.",
                ".THE AUTHORS HAVE NOTICED THAT THE BACKGROUND WAS",
                " ALWAYS HIGHER FOR EVENTS WITHIN THE T-OF-F PEAK",
                " THAN FOR THE REST OF THE T-OF-F SPECTRUM AND IT WAS",
                " RECOGNIZED ESSENTIAL TO CONSIDER THE BACKGROUND",
                " ASSOCIATED WITH THE PART OF THE T-OF-F BEING",
                " ANALYSED.",
                " A CORRECTION FOR THIS VARIABLE BACKGROUND WAS APPLIED",
                " WHICH RESULTED IN AN INCREASE OF THE NU VALUES GIVEN",
                " IN JNE,23,257.",
                ".IN A THIRD MEASUREMENT TO CHECK THESE CORRECTIONS",
                " THIS WAS NOT CONFIRMED AND IT WAS RATHER THE FIRST",
                " SET OF DATA THAT WAS CONFIRMED. THEREFORE THE DATA",
                " ARE ONCE AGAIN UPDATED IN THE PRIVATE COMMUNICATION",
                " OF FREHAUT."
